name: HTML Application Model
description: A model for building HTML applications

name: Action
description: Actions form a hierarchy. Application pages are generated from actions.

name: inline
description: Inline action's content is displayed instead of an action link in navigation panels.

name: modalActivator
description: Inline action's content is displayed in a modal dialog which opens on a click on the action's link.

name: sectionColumns
description: Applicable to section style "Card". Defines how many columns shall be in a row of section cards.

name: sectionStyle
description: Defines how to generate section children.

name: createLink
description: Creates a link pointing to this action and populated with action's text, icon, tooltip, and uuid attributes.

name: anonymous
description: Actions which are not shown in the containing action UI, but for which pages are generated and can be explicitly referenced, e.g. from content.

name: floatLeftNavigation
description: Float left navigation panel.

name: floatRightNavigation
description: Float right navigation panel.

name: leftNavigation
description: Left navigation panel

name: navigation
description: Navigation items are displayed in the footer the root action, in the navigation bar for the principal action, and in the content panel navigation bar for the active action.

name: resources
description: Resources referenced by the page. Resource names are resolved relative to the page location.

name: rightNavigation
description: Right navigation panel.

name: sections
description: Actions which are generated into content sections. Id's of section actions are used to create URL fragments.

name: breadcrumb

name: floatLeftNavigation

name: floatRightNavigation

name: leftNavigation

description: Application page consisting of several parts - header, navigation bar, navigation panel, content panel, and footer. Page extends Tag, but ``name`` attribute shall not be used - it defaults to ``div``.

name: header

name: navigationBar
description: Navigation bar is displayed below the header.

name: navigationPanel
description: Navigation panel is positioned on the left of the content panel below the navigation bar.
